import tensorflow as tf

a = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)
b = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)
c = a + b

with tf.Session() as sess:
    print(c.eval(feed_dict={a:1.0})) # I did not feed any value to

                                     # evaluating `c`

body:
Are you sure you are feeding a value into the placeholder? I get this error when I don't feed a value into the placeholder at all. Here is an example which generates an error message similar to yours.

```python
import tensorflow as tf

a = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)
b = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)
c = a + b

with tf.Session() as sess:
    print(c.eval(feed_dict={a:1.0})) # I did not feed any value to
                                     # `b` which is required for
                                     # evaluating `c`
```
